**LAUGHING CONFESSION:** A 19-year-old Mississippi man is charged with [**torching the state’s largest synagogue**](https://www.foxnews.com/us/mississippi-synagogue-arson-suspects-dad-turns-him-after-laughing-confession-fbi-says) in an antisemitic attack, the FBI says. Stephen Pittman allegedly set the fire after calling it "the synagogue of Satan," then laughed while confessing to his father, who turned him in. The historic Beth Israel Congregation suffered heavy damage; prosecutors are seeking severe penalties.

**COIN OF THE REALM:** Former NYC Mayor Eric Adams warned of rising antisemitism and anti-Americanism, unveiling a New York City [**digital coin to fund education, awareness, and scholarships**](https://www.foxbusiness.com/media/eric-adams-says-new-york-city-coin-fund-fight-against-antisemitism-anti-americanism) without raising taxes. Adams says blockchain proceeds would support antisemitism education, crypto training for students, and aid underserved youth—while positioning New York as a global cryptocurrency hub despite policy reversals by the new administration.

