**NUTTY PROFESSOR:** A Columbia University professor accused Israel of [**instigating Iran’s violent protests**](https://www.foxnews.com/us/iran-protests-instigated-by-israel-distract-from-gaza-genocide-columbia-professor-claims), claiming Mossad agents are embedded among demonstrators to undermine Tehran and distract from Gaza. Hamid Dabashi cited social media posts and alleged Israeli flags in protests. Columbia distanced itself from his remarks amid ongoing scrutiny over antisemitism and campus activism tied to the Israel-Hamas war.

**GUEST EDITORIAL:** Film producer Anita Friedman, whose "Among Neighbors" is now playing in select theaters, writes that Holocaust remembrance is [**more important than ever**](https://www.foxnews.com/opinion/why-holocaust-remembrance-matters-history-rewritten-antisemitism-surges) with history being actively rewritten by antisemites.

